quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  2,26,"Behold! Allah does not disdain to set forth a similitude even of a gnat, or anything lower or higher; and as for those who believe, they know that it is truth from the Lord; but as for those who disbelieve, they say, \"What is it that Allah means by t"
  2,27,"Those who break Allah´s covenant after the fixing thereof, and cut asunder what Allah has ordered to be joined, and do evil in the earth, these it is who are losers"
  2,28,"How can you disbelieve in Allah, when you were dead and He made you alive, and then He will cause you to die, and then make you alive again, and then to Him will you return"
  2,29,"It is He who created for you all that is in the earth, and He designed the heavens also and fashioned (ordered) them as seven heavens; and He knows all things"
  2,30,"And when your Lord said unto the angels, \"I am about to place a Vicegerent (Agent, Successor, Inheritor) in the earth,\" they said, \"Will you place therein one who will do evil therein and shed blood? While we celebrate Thy praise and glorif"
  2,31,"And He taught Adam the Names (qualities), all of them; then He propounded them to the angels and said, \"Declare to Me the names of these, if you are truthful"
  2,32,"They said, \"Glory be to Thee! No knowledge is ours but what Thou Thyself have taught us, verily, you are the Knower, the Wise"
  2,33,"Said the Lord, \"O Adam declare to them the Names;\" and when he had declared to them the Names, He said, \"Did I not say to you, I know the secrets of the heavens and of the earth, and I know what you reveal and what you conceal"
  2,34,"And when we said to the angels, \"Bow down before Adam,\" they bowed before him save only Iblis, who refused and was too proud and became one of the disbelievers"
  2,35,"And we said, \"O Adam dwell, you and your wife, in Paradise, and eat there from amply as you wish; but do not draw near this tree or you will be of the transgressors"
  2,36,"But Satan made them backslide there from and drove them out from what they were in, and We said, \"Go down, one of you the enemy of the other, and in the earth there is an abode and a provision for a time"
  2,37,"And Adam obtained certain words (revelations) from his Lord, and He relented towards him, for He is the Relenting, the Compassionate"
  2,38,"We said, \"Go down there from altogether and per chance (or possibly) there may come from Me a Guidance, and whoever follows My Guidance, no fear is theirs, nor shall they grieve"
  2,39,"But those who disbelieve, and call Our signs lies, they are the fellows of the Fire, they shall dwell therein for ever"
  2,40,"O you children of Israel! Remember My favours which I have favoured you with; fulfil My Covenant and I will fulfil your covenant; therefore, fear Me"
  2,41,"Believe in what I have revealed, verifying what you have got, and be not the first to disbelieve in it, and do not barter My signs for a little price, and keep your duty to Me"
  2,42,"Cloak not truth with vanity and falsehood, nor knowingly hide the truth"
  2,43,"Be steadfast in worship, give alms, and bow down with those who bow"